The images are not signed correctly for `registry.access.redhat.com/ubi8/ubi:latest`, that needs to be reported to the producer/publisher of those images.

---

> But the annotation were not present in older images

They would never be present in the `ubi:latest` image, they should be present in the signature-storage sort-of-artifacts.

And, yes, that’s up to whoever created those signatures.

For the current `:latest` pointing at `sha256:2f698e145dd30ac9f611b8984b910640bc210fae476dc36aa9ba200fad2a30ed`, and (guessing) the amd64 instance (in the future, please report the precise digests of affected images!), I now see:
